task.summary: Default task
Found issue with transposed boolean arguments. Added support for anonymous functions in QDL. ISO 6429 improvements.
reworked stem assignments. Bunch of stuff (newer code deplaced older code, which is still intact in ase we want to revert.) Much cleaner and leaner. Want to get it in github just in case.
Found and fixed an edge case. Updated out of date documentation. Allow for default values in slices. More regression tests.
Mostly making sure everything (in particular the documentation which git seems to miss regularly) end up pushed.
Had a system crash and had to reconstruct a few things. Putting it in git for safe keeping.
Found and fixed small bug with passing certain arguments to scripts. Removed annoying debug statements still in DB connection classes.

Found a bug in how (in certain cases) script arguments are not propagated correctly in QDL. Added block for better scoping of variables. Finally found and fixed annoying ISO 6429 bug. Experimental support for lists as indices.
Fixes for CIL-1012, CIL-1002
Updated some help. added flag to debug util so the log messages look better.
CIL-1011 support. Final checkin of stuff before cutting 5.1.4.

Changed how indices were being returned from a utility. Updates to documentation. Figured out how to do command line conversions of Libre Office to PDFs so I won't ever forget to update those again in a release. :) :) :)
Lots of documentation upgrades. Found an edge case in writing and example and fixed it with refgression tests.
Mostly changed documentation.
tweaked a few utilities. More help.
Fixed issue with try ... catch statements. Added more tests
A few small tweak. Added some regression tests. Mostly reformatting/editing help.
More documentation updates.
Mostly redoing help which in turn caused a few usability tweaks (in the )buffer command). improved serialization.
CIL-943, device flow support
Help updates. Changed how certain exceptions are thrown so there is better logging.
CIL-934 (device flow) part 3
QDl documentation. twiddled some exceptions to regularize their use.
Fixed a few minor things (mis-spellings in comments) and added comments to unit tests.
Added floor and ceiling functions to QDL (way overdue) since I have a little time to play catch up. Documented.
CIL-607, Updated nano syntax files. Added a test.
Mostly quality of life issues for the CLI. Added support for storing a result set and using it. Added tiny tweak to parser, which caused the whole thing to get rebuilt.

Many changes relating to improving searchs in the CLI. Now you can issue searches by approval status or approver (for clients) and generally search on any field with date ranges. Storing these as results sets to be consumed later is also supported.
Adding back in Derby support. Slight bit of genericizing since the SQL calls were a bit too optimized for MySQL.
Finally fixed an annoying test for printing a string.
Tidying up before 5.2.1
Tweaked parser. Added a few tests. Currently up to 1300+ actual QDL tests. Added RFC 7636 support.
Edge case with mondic QDL operators. Fixed and regression test.
Updated java mail jar. Wasn't sure if latest parser build was currently in git, so redid it and am adding it.
improved and extended QDL subset function. With tests and documentation.
Tightened up subsetting code. Documentation and tests. Mostly tweaked the error messages so they have a more consistent look and feel in certain cases.

Cleanup since 5.2.1 is out the door. Changed how missing arguments to QDL are intercepted so user gets consistent messages. Test suites had some very old junit annotations that are no longer needed and have been removed (which also removes a ton of warnings when running tests).

More cleanup: Changed parser to use variables for operators rather than hard coding them. Better handling of missing variable messages, which should help with tracking down errors in complex expressions. Updated documentation.
Found and fixed annoyting typo in lexer.
wikked kewl enhancement to working with indices in QDL. Extends what is there, so no impact on existing code.
Added an axis operator. tests and documentation.
Few tweaks to parser and the terminal. Added query for current terminal to workspace.
Added a reserved word for QDL, but not doing anything with it. Just don't want people to start using it as, e.g. a variable.
Updating a few names of things. Refactoring.
Tiny tweaks getting ready for 5.2.2
Found a real edge case for comparing two values. Improved a function. Mostly this is cleanup running up to 5.2.2.
Found another edge case, added slew of unit tests for parsing (ongoing, long term task) in QDL.

Yikes! Upgrade to junit changed how assert was handled, effectively making a slew of my regression tests (potentially) giving false positives. QDL tests (rocking it at over 1400) amended. All was working, so no red flags and now that class of error detection has been replaced.
